note: pokemon should be added in reverse order so the forward references of evolution don't point to as-yet-unloaded pokemon

species.name: Mew
species.description: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.

species.name: Mewtwo
species.description: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

species.name: Dragonite
species.description: An extremely rarely seen marine POKEMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

species.name: Dragonair
species.description: A mystical POKEMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

species.name: Dratini
species.description: Long considered a mythical POKEMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

species.name: Moltres
species.description: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

species.name: Zapdos
species.description: A legendary bird POKEMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

species.name: Articuno
species.description: A legendary bird POKEMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

species.name: Snorlax
species.description: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

species.name: Aerodactyl
species.description: A ferocious, prehistoric POKEMON that goes for the enemy's throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

species.name: Kabutops
species.description: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

species.name: Kabuto
species.description: A POKEMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

species.name: Omastar
species.description: A prehistoric POKEMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

species.name: Omanyte
species.description: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.

species.name: Porygon
species.description: A POKEMON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

species.name: Flareon
species.description: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

species.name: Jolteon
species.description: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000-volt lightning bolts.

species.name: Vaporeon
species.description: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

species.name: Eevee
species.description: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.

species.name: Ditto
species.description: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

species.name: Lapras
species.description: A POKEMON that has been over hunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.

species.name: Gyarados
species.description: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

species.name: Magikarp
species.description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

species.name: Tauros
species.description: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

species.name: Pinsir
species.description: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

species.name: Magmar
species.description: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

species.name: Electabuzz
species.description: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

species.name: Jinx
species.description: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

species.name: Scyther
species.description: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can created the illusion that there is more than one.

species.name: Mr. Mime
species.description: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

species.name: Starmie
species.description: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

species.name: Staryu
species.description: An enigmatic POKEMON that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

species.name: Seaking
species.description: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

species.name: Goldeen
species.description: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

species.name: Seadra
species.description: Capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

species.name: Horsea
species.description: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

species.name: Kangaskhan
species.description: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective punch until it is 3 years old.

species.name: Tangela
species.description: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. Its vines shake as it walks.

species.name: Chansey
species.description: A rare and elusive POKEMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

species.name: Rhydon
species.description: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

species.name: Rhyhorn
species.description: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

species.name: Weezing
species.description: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

species.name: Koffing
species.description: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

species.name: Lickitung
species.description: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

species.name: Hitmonchan
species.description: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

species.name: Hitmonlee
species.description: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

species.name: Marowak
species.description: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

species.name: Cubone
species.description: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKEMON's real face.

note: TALK TO RICH AND JON ABOUT POSSIBILITY OF INCLUDING LEVEL ZERO FOR STONE EVOLUTION MOVES

species.name: Exeggutor
species.description: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

species.name: Exeggcute
species.description: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

species.name: Electrode
species.description: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

species.name: Voltorb
species.description: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Pokeball, they have zapped many people.

species.name: Kingler
species.description: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

species.name: Krabby
species.description: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

species.name: Hypno
species.description: When it locks eyes with and enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.

species.name: Drowzee
species.description: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

species.name: Onix
species.description: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to diamond, but colored black.

species.name: Gengar
species.description: Under a full moon, this POKEMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

species.name: Haunter
species.description: Because of its ability to slip through Detect walls, it is said to be from another dimension.

species.name: Gastly
species.description: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKEMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

species.name: Cloyster
species.description: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

species.name: Shellder
species.description: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

species.name: Muk
species.description: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

species.name: Grimer
species.description: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

species.name: Dewgong
species.description: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

species.name: Seel
species.description: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

species.name: Dodrio
species.description: Using its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

species.name: Doduo
species.description: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

species.name: Farfetch'd
species.description: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

species.name: Magneton
species.description: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

species.name: Magnemite
species.description: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

species.name: Slowbro
species.description: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.

species.name: Slowpoke
species.description: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

species.name: Rapidash
species.description: Very competitive, this POKEMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

species.name: Ponyta
species.description: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time

species.name: Golem
species.description: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

species.name: Graveler
species.description: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

species.name: Geodude
species.description: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

species.name: Tentacruel
species.description: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

species.name: Tentacool
species.description: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

species.name: Victreebel
species.description: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

species.name: Weepinbell
species.description: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

species.name: Bellsprout
species.description: A carnivorous Pokemon that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

species.name: Machamp
species.description: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

species.name: Machoke
species.description: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

species.name: Machop
species.description: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

species.name: Alakazam
species.description: Its brain can outperform a super-computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

species.name: Kadabra
species.description: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

species.name: Abra
species.description: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

species.name: Poliwrath
species.description: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

species.name: Poliwhirl
species.description: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

species.name: Poliwag
species.description: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

species.name: Arcanine
species.description: A POKEMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

species.name: Growlithe
species.description: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

species.name: Primeape
species.description: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

species.name: Mankey
species.description: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

species.name: Golduck
species.description: Often seen swimming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

species.name: Psyduck
species.description: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKEMON will use psychokinetic powers.

species.name: Persian
species.description: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

species.name: Meowth
species.description: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

species.name: Dugtrio
species.description: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

species.name: Diglett
species.description: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

species.name: Venomoth
species.description: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

species.name: Venonat
species.description: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

species.name: Parasect
species.description: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

species.name: Paras
species.description: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

species.name: Vileplume
species.description: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

species.name: Gloom
species.description: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

species.name: Oddish
species.description: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

species.name: Golbat
species.description: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

species.name: Zubat
species.description: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

species.name: Wigglytuff
species.description: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

species.name: Jigglypuff
species.description: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

species.name: Ninetales
species.description: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

species.name: Vulpix
species.description: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

species.name: Clefable
species.description: A timid fairy POKEMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

species.name: Clefairy
species.description: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

species.name: Nidoking
species.description: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.

species.name: Nidorino
species.description: An aggressive POKEMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

species.name: Nidoran (M)
species.description: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful it secreted venom.

species.name: Nidoqueen
species.description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

species.name: Nidorina
species.description: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

species.name: Nidoran (F)
species.description: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKEMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

species.name: Sandslash
species.description: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

species.name: Sandshrew
species.description: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

species.name: Raichu
species.description: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.

species.name: Pikachu
species.description: When several of these POKMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

species.name: Arbok
species.description: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

species.name: Ekans
species.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

species.name: Fearow
species.description: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

species.name: Spearow
species.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

species.name: Raticate
species.description: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

species.name: Rattata
species.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

species.name: Pidgeot
species.description: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.

species.name: Pidgeotto
species.description: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.

species.name: Pidgey
species.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

species.name: Beedrill
species.description: Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.

species.name: Kakuna
species.description: Almost incapable of moving, this POKMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

species.name: Weedle
species.description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

species.name: Butterfree
species.description: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

species.name: Metapod
species.description: This POKMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

species.name: Caterpie
species.description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

species.name: Blastoise
species.description: A brutal POKMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

species.name: Wartortle
species.description: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

species.name: Squirtle
species.description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

species.name: Charizard
species.description: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

species.name: Charmeleon
species.description: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels

species.name: Charmander
species.description: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

species.name: Venusaur
species.description: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

species.name: Ivysaur
species.description: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

species.name: Bulbasaur
species.description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKMON.
